Rating: 1
This salad was a hit at our thanksgiving dinner. The recipe for the dressing was not sweet enough nor did it thicken enought to be satisfactory as a salad dressing. To remedy this, I brought the juice just to a boil and added 2 tablespoons of Arrowroot.( corn starch could be used but arrowroot makes a clear glaze type sauce). Also to sweeten to taste I added two droppers of stevia and one pkt of sweet and low. The dressing was more palatable and more to my liking for thickness. Increasing the amount of dried cranberries and using mandarine oranges makes a very attractive dressing. This recipe makes a very pretty salad when the dressing is served over mixed greens.

